text: I've been using this app for a long time now. I find it very helpful and easy to use. It can really help me see trends in my moods and sleep patterns, especially after I change my medication dose. I have Bipolar 2 and BPD plus other health issues and this app helps me track all these. I'll be becoming a forever patron as soon as my free trial is over.

feature request: the ability to undo making a selection. I've accidentally tapped buttons for past days when I don't remember what my actual symptoms were, and I'd rather there be a blank spot than inaccurate data.  overall, a good app. might update this review after I've played around with the custom tracking points more.
replyText: Thanks for your review!  I'm making some updates to the app this weekend- I'll try to get this fix in as well- you're one of many who have suggested it :)  Hopefully an update will be available next week.

text: It feels weird to leave such a short review after discussing this app on a Reddit post, then having a very elaborate back and forth conversation with the dev for a few days.  The tracking options are amazing and the default tracking options are more than enough to get you started. You'll probably add a few more as you go but it's really nice to quickly start tracking things. With beautiful charts to help you see possible trends.  I respect the devs privacy concerns, though I do have feature request that needs the internet permission. They are very responsive and genuinely happy to discuss your concerns with you. This dev is very proud of this project and that energy is a bit infectious.   I'll probably (not?) write a more detailed review about the app itself but the experience of picking the dev's mind was very enjoyable. Gah, I can't say enough good things about this app!

After recently being diagnosed with Bipolar, this app has helped me to track my moods. It's a simple tool to use and easily adjusted. Graphs are helpful for my doctor to see while i am stabilizing on my medication.

I don't have bipolar disorder, I have a thyroid disorder that causes mental and physical symptoms. This app works really well for me for keeping track of how I am feeling each day so I can communicate properly with my doctor about how my medicine and disorder affect me. This app is great!

Been using the free version if this app for almost a month and it has made a significant difference in my stress levels. It makes it so easy to log my moods and medication. A live saver for a struggling bi polar.

I'm starting to use this to track my mood, even though I'm not bipolar, but I still struggle with anxiety, depression, and meltdowns. It's helpful to be able to log what caused me to reach different levels. My therapist wants me to log my mood each day and log notes about what I did that day, and this does the job really well so far!

This app has been a good help in documenting my mood patterns for the past few months. I have tweaked this a bit to include my exercise & yoga routines in the Medications section.   But unfortunately, I am having this problme qith the app. I can't seem to encode my mood data for December 9. Is there any bug relating to this, or the free versiob only allows me up to this point? Admin, please please, I need your answers!
replyText: The app doesn't let you log data for future dates (Dec 9).  It is now Dec 7 in the US and Dec 8 in the Pacific/Asia.  Could you reach out to me over email- it will be easier to help troubleshoot.  info@emoodtracker.com

text: So far I like the app, it's definitely better than some of the other ones out there. I do wish there was a way to lock the app itself and a way to customize some small things, but thats not going to deter me from using it.

Great resource for tracking moods and medication adherence. The graphs are excellent in viewing trends and frequency and/or duration of episodes and their symptoms. Would definitely recommend to someone looking to manage bipolar disorder.

This app is incredible, I'm so thankful for it. Having two young children, I often don't have time to think about and reflect on my day but this helps me to remember and it helps my doctor and I create plans specifically for me based on my routine of moods.
I love this app. Clearly lots of  work went into it. I only had to add hypomania and dysphoria (I tend to swing lightly but often). Anyone know how to synch phone with laptop?
replyText: Thanks for your review!  There is no app available (yet!) for desktop/laptop so no syncing now.  You can export your data from the settings screen however.  If you download and rename the .emoods file with extension .zip you can access CSV data which can be opened in excel.  Email if you have more questions - info@emoodtracker.com

text: I enjoy using this app to track medications and mood. It's particularly useful to help determine if mood changes are associated with life changes or medication changes. This is the best mood+med tracker app.
I have used this app for a few years now. I don't like the way the graph is, I find it difficult to keep track. It would be good if there were other options available
Definitely helps me to keep track of my moods and to understand why, when, how often and what sets me off. Definitely recommended for Bipolar/Depression/Anxiety/BPD patients
It's really amazing app. Helps  alot to keep track of moods, sleeping hours and tablets taken. Thanks alot!
This is a nice simple way of tracking my moods. Has help me be more aware of the changes and also maybe helping me to spot my highs which I find difficult.
So far so good ! Looking forward to seeing my moods. Not for bipolar but therapist recommended tracking

Very simple and easy to use. It incorporates everything you need to track everything on a daily basis. The graph feature is very handy and provides a great way to visualize your moods over time. Would definitely recommend app!
Good for tracking my mood swings. Helps my friends know how I'm feeling today. xxx
So far, it is helpful with tracking minutiae through the day. The app also helps keeping track of my constant med changes, as I am newly diagnosed.
I am very excited to try this for the first 15 days, it looks very promising. If I'm still using it after that I will become a patron, your hard work doesn't go unnoticed!
replyText: Thank you so much!  Feel free to reach out any time with questions or suggestions:  info@emoodtracker.com

text: Good app, I would personally  find it better  if I could log exercise, meditation, and healthy eating (i.e. a tick box).  The more info lodged the better the data outcome

I have BPD and my psychiatrist is suspecting Bipolar II as well so this app is really good for keeping an eye on my moods and hopefully it'll help to see how I respond to mood stabilizers in the future.

This app is amazing! I don't use it for bipolar, i use it for my bpd. The mood tracking is amazing and the graphs are great for checking how your mood has been. It also tracks your medication, which is useful.
This app has helped me so much! I've tried other apps but this one is so simple and easy to use. I actually look forward to logging my information!
Best mood tracker I've tried. Clean interface, easily customised, thoughtful tools like auto-check for daily meds. Privacy policy is simple and upgrades are affordable. Nice work.
Just got this, need to leave a review to add custom tacking points. Hoping it has the ability to print data to take to appointments.  EDIT- Thank you for taking the time to reply.
replyText: You can definitely do this!  :) From the top "..." menu just click on "email report" and select a month.  You can mail to yourself to print or directly to your Dr/therapist

text: So far ok. Could use chronic illness. Pain level etc as well of a menstruation input.
replyText: Thanks for your review!  Menstruation is already on there which you can track by going to the settings screen and toggling it on under "default tracking points".  You can also use the two week trial to add chronic illness and pain level custom tracking points, which will still be there after the trial ends.  Reach out any time with questions.

text: Its very handy in keeping track of medications, and my mood. Its really helpful to see averages for things like sleep which makes it easier to keep track.
I was recently diagnosed as bipolar and while I don't understand my mood changes and triggers just yet , however the chart makes it easy for others to understand my moods.
An amazing way to track my moods. Love the ability to graph and email myself a report. Excellent app and so far the best I've tried and seen available.
Just beginning use of this, but will see how this helps with my symptoms.
Just started using, not sure what I think yet but seems really helpful and seems to work just fine so far.
Nice little app. Gonna give it a try and see how things go.
replyText: Thanks for your review.  Please reach out any time if I can help answer any questions about the app!  -Jon (app developer)  info@emoodtracker.com

text: This is just the app i was looking for , my only wish was that the graph had a option for a pie chart layout ... the app is gonna please my therapist , cant wait to share
I downloaded this for my husband to track his moods. We're working with a therapist to come to a diagnosis and treatment plan for him. I'm hoping this helps us.
This is one of the better apps I've used! I really like that you can print out the log and give it to your doctor.
replyText: Thanks so much for your review!  Feel free to reach out any time with suggestions for the app :)  info@emoodtracker.com -Jon (app creator)

text: As someone with borderline personality it works quite well! The graphs are helpful to track mood.
I love this app. It helps me so much. I now can recognize patterns in my emotions!
